asparagus-setaceus.name: Asparagus fern
asparagus-setaceus.description: A branching perennial herb with tough green aerial stems which are sparsely covered with spines.

syngonium-podophyllum.name: Arrowhead plant
syngonium-podophyllum.description: A climbing plant with arrow-shaped leaves.

aspidistra-elatior.name: Cast iron plant
aspidistra-elatior.description: A perennial with glossy dark leaves and cream-colored flowers.

monstera-deliciosa.name: Cheese plant
monstera-deliciosa.description: A tropical flowering plant with distinctive holes in its leaves.

epipremnum-aureum.name: Devil's vine
epipremnum-aureum.description: A common houseplant known for its heartiness and difficulty to kill.

sedum-morganianum.name: Donkey's tail
sedum-morganianum.description: A succulent that grows out in vines of fleshy, blue-green leaves.

hedera-helix.name: English ivy
hedera-helix.description: A rampantly growing and hearty vine that can often be found taking over gardens, walls, and tree trunks.

ficus-lyrata.name: Fiddle-leaf fig
ficus-lyrata.description: A stalky plant identified by its distinctive fiddle-shaped leaves.

crassula-ovata.name: Jade plant
crassula-ovata.description: A succulent known as one of the most common houseplants. It has thick branches with thick, shiny, smooth leaves.

sedum-rubrotinctum.name: Jelly bean plant
sedum-rubrotinctum.description: A succulent with small, red-green leaves shaped like jelly beans.

dracaena-sanderiana.name: Lucky bamboo
dracaena-sanderiana.description: A water-loving plant that grows very quickly given adequate sunlight and water.

pachira-aquatica.name: Money tree
pachira-aquatica.description: A tree-like plant with star-shaped leaves. The base of the plant is often braided together to allow the plant to grow vertically.

gymnocalycium-mihanovichii.name: Moon cactus
gymnocalycium-mihanovichii.description: A succulent identified by a colorful cactus bulb on top of a cactus stalk.

chamaedorea-elegans.name: Parlor palm
chamaedorea-elegans.description: A woody plant with a slender green trunk with long, skinny palm leaves.

maranta-leuconeura.name: Prayer plants
maranta-leuconeura.description: A broad and clumping plant named for how its leaves lay flat during the day but stand erect at night as if in prayer.

ficus-elastica.name: Rubber plant
ficus-elastica.description: A large tree-like plant with a stout trunk and broad, shiny leaves.

dracaena-trifasciata.name: Snake plant
dracaena-trifasciata.description: An extremely common houseplant, having long green-yellow leaves that grow vertically.

chlorophytum-comosum.name: Spider plant
chlorophytum-comosum.description: A hanging plant that grows pups on the hanging vines.

senecio-rowleyanus.name: String of pearls
senecio-rowleyanus.description: A hanging succulent with hanging vines decorated by green beads.

ficus-benjamina.name: Weeping fig
ficus-benjamina.description: A ficus with graceful, drooping branchlets and glossy leaves.

yucca-elephantipes.name: Yucca plant
yucca-elephantipes.description: A large plant with thick, barky trunks with pointed palms at its top.

haworthiopsis-attenuata.name: Zebra plant
haworthiopsis-attenuata.description: A small and easily manageable plant identifiable by its green and white leaves.

zamioculcas-zamiifolia.name: ZZ plant
zamioculcas-zamiifolia.description: A branching plant with tough stalks and ovular, shiny leaves.

soleirolia-soleirolii.name: Baby's tears plant
soleirolia-soleirolii.description: A hanging plant that drapes in vines of many tiny, green leaves.

strelitzia-reginae.name: Bird of paradise plant
strelitzia-reginae.description: A flowering plant known for its vibrant flowers that resemble birds.

asplenium-nidus.name: Bird's nest fern
asplenium-nidus.description: A light-green and plain looking plant with large simple fronds for leaves.

nephrolepis-exaltata.name: Sword fern
nephrolepis-exaltata.description: A distinctive fern recognizable for its dark green fronds that spread out radially from its base.

radermachera-sinica.name: China doll plant
radermachera-sinica.description: A tree-like plant with compact, shiny leaves.

dracaena-marginata.name: Dragon tree
dracaena-marginata.description: A slow-growing, tall plant with long, thin fronds.

mimosa-pudica.name: Sensitive plant
mimosa-pudica.description: A simple looking plant with thin stalks named after how the plant droops reactively after it has been touched.

hoya-kerrii.name: Lucky-heart plant
hoya-kerrii.description: A succulent named for its fleshy, green body shaped like a heart.

calathea-crocata.name: Eternal flame plant
calathea-crocata.description: A plant known for letting their owners know when to go to bed, as its leaves close up in the evening. It has darkly colored leaves and a distinct golden-yellow flower.

vriesea-splendens.name: Flaming sword bromeliad
vriesea-splendens.description: A simple looking plant that flowers with a vibrant, long flower that can be red, orange, yellow, or a mix.

euphorbia-pulcherrima.name: Poinsettia
euphorbia-pulcherrima.description: A festive plant with bright red leaves and that is usually given during the Christmas season.

guzmania-lingulata.name: Scarlet star plant
guzmania-lingulata.description: A bromelaid with long, thin leaves and a vibrant star-shaped flower.

pilea-cadierei.name: Aluminum plant
pilea-cadierei.description: A plant with bushy and silver-marked leaves that is said to be easy to take care of.

dracaena-fragrans.name: Corn plant
dracaena-fragrans.description: A hearty, unbranched, tree-like plant with sword-shaped, arching leaves.

alocasia-amazonica.name: Amazonian elephant's ear
alocasia-amazonica.description: A plant identifiable by its large, veiny leaves.

maranta-makoyana.name: Peacock plant
maranta-makoyana.description: A perennial with round, pale, glossy green leaves.

dionaea-muscipula.name: Venus fly trap
dionaea-muscipula.description: A carnivorous plant with multiple mandibles that snap shut when it feels prey.

opuntia-microdasys.name: Bunny ear cactus
opuntia-microdasys.description: A wide and thin cactus that grows out in successive wide, thin disks.

schlumbergera-bridgesii.name: Christmas cactus
schlumbergera-bridgesii.description: A clumping, drooping plant that blooms vibrantly throughout in shades of red, white, yellow, pink, or purple.

kalanchoe-tomentosa.name: Panda plant
kalanchoe-tomentosa.description: A small succulent recognized by its green, fleshy, fuzzy leaves.

bryophyllum-daigremontianum.name: Mother of thousands
bryophyllum-daigremontianum.description: A wide plant most recognizable by the many baby plantlets that grow off the sides of its leaves.

euphorbia-lactea.name: Coral cactus
euphorbia-lactea.description: A large cactus that grows into a single wavy and rigid shape resemblant of coral.
